{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3>Youâ€™ll learn how to:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>code in HTML, CSS &#x26; Javascript</li>\n<li>pull, commit and push to Github</li>\n<li>host an app on Heroku</li>\n<li>save time using ninja computer shortcuts</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>hello world<h3>\n<p><canvas id=\"canvas\"></canvas></p>\n<script>\n  var canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');\n  var ctx = canvas.getContext(\"2d\");\n\n  let width = window.innerWidth;\n  let height = window.innerHeight;\n\n  canvas.width = width;\n  canvas.height = height;\n\n  let t = 0;\n\n\n  function animate(){\n\n    // clear the canvas\n    // ctx.clearRect(0, 0, width, height)\n\n    let size = 5;\n\n    // draw 10 columns\n    for(let j = 0; j <= 100; j++){\n\n      // draw a column\n      for (let i = 0; i <= 100; i++){\n\n        let margin = size * 2 ;\n        let x;\n        let y;\n\n\n        ctx.beginPath();\n        ctx.rect(\n          (j + 1) * margin  ,\n          (i + 1) * margin,\n          size * Math.sin(t*i/100),\n          size * Math.sin(t*j/100)\n         );\n         ctx.translate((size/2),(size/2))\n        ctx.fill();\n        ctx.closePath();\n      }\n\n    }\n\n    // tell the browser to iterate\n    window.requestAnimationFrame(animate)\n    t++;\n  }\n\n  animate();\n</script>","frontmatter":{"title":"Rapid prototyping","duration":"2 day intensive","description":"Learn to empower yourself and others around you by visualising your ideas as fully functioning prototypes hosted on the internet."}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/courses/rapid-prototyping/"}}